video:video.video:description: Former NFL player Gosder Cherilus has been arraigned in court, following allegations that he drunkenly hit one man and urinated on another during a flight from Boston to Dublin, forcing the flight to return to the airport.

video:video.video:title: Two trains collide in Colorado, spilling fuel and injuring two crew members
video:video.video:description: Two trains have collided in Boulder, Colorado. Fuel spilled into a creek and two crew members have what police say are minor injuries.

video:video.video:title: Swift tour resumes in London after cancellations
video:video.video:description: Excited Taylor Swift fans are arriving at Wembley Arena for the singer's first show after three concerts in Vienna were canceled after police arrested three Islamic State-inspired extremists they believed were planning to attack the venue.

video:video.video:title: Hotel fire in South Korea kills at least 7 people and injures 12
video:video.video:description: Seven people died and 12 others were injured after a fire broke out at a hotel in the South Korean city of Bucheon, officials said.

video:video.video:title: Surfers compete on powerful waves of over 13 feet in Brazil's Itacoatiara Big Wave event
video:video.video:description: The Brazilian Navy's alert for rough seas in Rio de Janeiro gave the green light for the sixth edition of Itacoatiara Big Wave surf event, attracting national and international surfers to compete in the powerful waves over 13 feet of Itacoatiara beach.

video:video.video:title: Hezbollah attack on Israel was delayed to give Gaza cease-fire talks a chance, Nasrallah says
video:video.video:description: Hezbollah's leader said Sunday that the group delayed its response for the killing of one of their commanders in Beirut to give a chance for potential ceasefire negotiations.

video:video.video:title: Advancing on three fronts, Madeira wildfire forces at least 100 people to evacuate
video:video.video:description: An uncontrolled fire on the Portuguese island of Madeira was burning for a fifth consecutive day on Sunday.

video:video.video:title: Kamala Harris celebrates the late Rep. Sheila Jackson Lee as a 'force of nature'
video:video.video:description: Vice President Kamala Harris on Thursday eulogized longtime U.S. Rep. Sheila Jackson Lee as a “force of nature” as memorials for the longtime Democratic lawmaker drew to a close.

video:video.video:title: Former MFP leader: 'absolutely proud of what I have achieved' following dissolution of party by court
video:video.video:description: A court in Thailand on Wednesday ordered the dissolution of the progressive Move Forward Party, which finished first in last year's general election, saying it violated the constitution by proposing an amendment of a law against defaming the country’s royal family.

video:video.video:title: Plane crash in Brazil kills all 61 people aboard, airliner says
video:video.video:description: A passenger plane with 61 people aboard crashed into a gated residential community in Brazil’s Sao Paulo state Friday, killing all aboard, the airline said.

video:video.video:description: Judges and magistrates on Wednesday joined a strike organised by federal court employees in Mexico to oppose the controversial proposal put forward by President Andrés Manuel López Obrador to overhaul the country's judicial system.

video:video.video:title: Trump sticks to familiar attack lines during speech billed as a significant economic address
video:video.video:description: His team billed the speech as a significant economic address, but Donald Trump made little effort to stay on message Wednesday in Asheville, North Carolina, choosing instead to stick to his familiar personal attacks against Democratic rival Kamala Harris.

video:video.video:title: Kamala Harris pledges reform of US immigration system if elected in November
video:video.video:description: US Vice President Kamala Harris has pledged to reform the country's immigration system if she is elected president in November.

video:video.video:description: Strong winds knocked nearly four dozen train cars off a track in North Dakota, part of a storm system that spurred reports of five tornadoes across the Dakotas.

video:video.video:description: Gunmen fatally shot at least 23 passengers after identifying them and taking them from buses, vehicles, and trucks in one of the deadliest attacks in restive southwestern Pakistan, police and officials said on Monday.
